{"cursor":"2736","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn computer science, an 'action language' is a language for specifying state\ntransition systems, and is commonly used to create formal models of the effects\nof actions on the world. Michael Gelfond, Vladimir Lifschitz (1998)\n\"[http://www.ep.liu.se/ea/cis/1998/016/ Action Languages]\", LinkÃ¶ping Electronic\nArticles in Computer and Information Science, vol '3', nr 16. Action\nlanguages are commonly used in the artificial intelligence and robotics domains,\nwhere they describe how actions affect the states of systems over time, and may\nbe used for automated planning. The best known action language is PDDL. Drew\nMcDermott, The Planning Domain Definition Language, Technical Report CVC TR-98-\n003/DCS TR-1165, Yale Center for Computational Vision and Control, Yale\nUniversity, 1998.\n\nAction languages fall into two classes: action description languages and action\nquery languages. Examples of the former include STRIPS, PDDL, Language A (a\ngeneralization of STRIPS; the propositional part of Pednault's ADL), Language B\n(an extension of A adding indirect effects, distinguishing static and dynamic\nlaws) and Language C (which adds indirect effects also, and does not assume that\nevery fluent is automatically \"inertial\"). There are also the Action Query\nLanguages P, Q and R. Several different algorithms exist for converting action\nlanguages, and in particular, action language C, to answer set\nprograms. Vladimir Lifschitz and Hudson Turner, (1998)\n\"[http://www.d.umn.edu/~hudson/papers/rtslp9.pdf Representing Transition Systems\nby Logic Programs]\". Martin Gebser, Torsten Grote and Torsten Schaub,\n(2010) \"[http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download;jsessionid=B8225EE564124-\nD21F30BDC44B05A702A?doi=10.1.1.185.4622&rep=rep1&type=pdf Coala: a compiler from\naction languages to ASP]\". Since modern answer-set solvers make use of\nboolean SAT algorithms to very rapidly ascertain satisfiability, this implies\nthat action languages can also enjoy the progress being made in the domain of\nboolean SAT solving.\n","linknr":183,"url":"Action_language","recorded":1374859789,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Action_language&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Action_language&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Programming_paradigm","/wiki/Agent-oriented_programming","/wiki/Aspect-oriented_programming","/wiki/Automata-based_programming","/wiki/Component-based_software_engineering","/wiki/Flow-based_programming","/wiki/Pipeline_programming","/wiki/Concatenative_programming_language","/wiki/Concurrent_computing","/wiki/Relativistic_programming","/wiki/Data-driven_programming","/wiki/Declarative_programming","/wiki/Imperative_programming","/wiki/Constraint_programming","/wiki/Dataflow_programming","/wiki/Spreadsheet","/wiki/Reactive_programming","/wiki/Category:Intensional_programming_languages","/wiki/Functional_programming","/wiki/Logic_programming","/wiki/Abductive_logic_programming","/wiki/Answer_set_programming","/wiki/Constraint_logic_programming","/wiki/Functional_logic_programming","/wiki/Inductive_logic_programming","/wiki/End-user_development","/wiki/Event-driven_programming","/wiki/Ser